Citation.sTitle: (p, q, T) properties, and apparent molar volumes V/ of ZnBr2 in methanol at T = (298.15 to 398.15) K and pressures up to p = 40 MPa
Citation.sAbstract: The (p, p, T) properties of pure methanol, the (p, p, T) properties and apparent molar volumes V/ of ZnBr2 in methanol at T = (298.15 to 398.15) K and pressures up to p = 40 MPa are reported, and apparent molar volumes have been evaluated. The experimental (p, p, T, m) values were described by an equation of state. For the solutions the experiments were carried out at molalities m = (0.05772, 0.37852, 0.71585 and 1.95061) mol.kg-1 of zinc bromide.
